            {
              "type": "reasoning",
              "is_native": true,
              "reasoning": "Good! Now I understand the repo. Let me provide a concise summary to the user as per my instructions to be brief.",
              "signature": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This is **Dodo** (formerly Dodo) - a Python-based platform for building stateful AI agents with advanced memory that can learn and self-improve over time.\n\n**Key features:**\n- Memory hierarchy with self-editing memory blocks\n- Multi-agent shared memory support\n- Sleep-time agents (background processing)\n- MCP tool integration\n- Filesystem attachment for document access\n- Long-running agent support with resumable streaming\n- Agent File (.af) format for portability\n\n**Tech stack:** Python 3.11+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, PostgreSQL/SQLite, OpenTelemetry, integrates with OpenAI/Anthropic/local models\n\n**Development:** Use `uv sync --all-extras` to install, `uv run dodo server` to run",
              "signature": null
            }
          ],
